<paragraph blockId="3.[714,1247,1520,1669]" lastBlockId="5.[151,684,170,412]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="12" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
Shrub 
<quantity box="[824,947,1520,1547]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5-1.5 m</quantity>
high. Young branchlets glabrous. Leaves nearly glabrous below, glabrous above, obovate or oblanceolate, 3.5-6.5 
<emphasis box="[1125,1140,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1146,1242,1581,1608]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5-2 cm</quantity>
, apex obtuse or rounded (and retuse), secondary veins usually prominulous. Inflorescences nearly glabrous to puberulent, 1- or few-flowered, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" unit="cm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.8">0.8- 1.5 cm</quantity>
long, pedicels 
<quantity box="[415,532,201,228]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5-3 mm</quantity>
long. Sepals glabrous to sparsely puberulent abaxially, glabrous adaxially, connate in proximal 1/3-1/2, the free portion broadly triangular, 
<quantity box="[550,683,293,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="1.15" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.8">0.8-1.5 mm</quantity>
long; petals white, densely appressed-puberulent abaxially, glabrous adaxially; ovaries like the follicles glabrous or nearly so.
</paragraph>
